<problem>
<statement>
<p> 
Note that vectors <m>\mathbf{x}_1=\begin{bmatrix}3\\1\end{bmatrix}</m> and <m>\mathbf{x}_2=\begin{bmatrix}-2\\1\end{bmatrix}</m> (and their scalar multiples) remain positioned along the same lines even as they change magnitude and direction.  This indicates that <m>\mathbf{x}_1</m> and <m>\mathbf{x}_2</m>, along with all of their scalar multiples, are eigenvectors of <m>A</m>.  What are the eigenvalues associated with these eigenvectors?
</p> 
