<p>
A natural question is this: does every square matrix have eigenvalues and eigenvectors?  We will address this question in later sections and there discover that the answer to this question is ``yes", provided that we permit eigenvalues and entries of eigenvectors to be complex numbers.  The next example is one that requires complex numbers.
</p> 


